Action-Oriented Version:
"Could you please assign a team member to:

Review the GitLab DEV environment upgraded to v17.5.5 last week

Confirm all systems are functioning as expected
This will help us proceed confidently with the production upgrade."

Formal Request Version:
"I'd like to request resource allocation to conduct a post-implementation review of the GitLab DEV environment (now on v17.5.5) prior to scheduling the production upgrade."

Collaborative Approach:
"To ensure a smooth production upgrade, let's have someone from the team review the DEV environment we upgraded to v17.5.5 last week. This will help identify any potential issues before they reach production."

Choose the version that best matches your organization's communication style. The key elements to include are:

The action taken (DEV upgrade to v17.5.5)

The request (review by a resource)

The purpose (preparing for production upgrade)
